      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Eroded Self</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nancy Stark letter on Jeffrey Rosen's April 30 article holds loss of privacy is least problem that those who spend their lives in front of computers face</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>So where is it written that gossiping, pursuing a romantic sexual liaison or cussing out the boss are activities that you're obliged to do in cyberspace? What about the water cooler, the telephone, the neighborhood pub? E-mail addicts might find it delightful to get out in the world and listen to laughter, see the sparkle in someone's eyes. Those who spend their lives in front of a computer have a serious problem, and loss of privacy is quite possibly the least of it.</p>
        <p>Nancy Stark  New York</p>
      </block>
